properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 2 at 2:48PM AKST until February 4 at 3:00AM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 8
inches. Winds gusting as high as 35 mph.

* WHERE...Northeast and eastern Gulf coast, and central and
southern inner channels including, Ketchikan, Petersburg,
Angoon, Pelican, and Yakutat.

* WHEN...From 9 AM Monday to 3 AM AKST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Wet snow will be
difficult to manage.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow will mix with or change to rain
through Monday evening. Rain on top of snow may continue to
cause travel impacts where there is a deep snow pack.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM MONDAY TO 3 AM AKST TUESDAY
